  "Endpoints are the boundary values a and b of a closed interval [a,b]. Absolute extrema can occur at endpoints, so they must always be checked.": "端点是封闭间隔[a,b] 的a和b的边界值。 端点可以发生绝对extrema, 因此必须始终检查 。",
  "A company manufactures boxes to ship products. Each box must have a volume of 500 cm^3 with a square base. What base dimension minimizes the surface area?": "公司制造箱装产品,每个箱必须有500立方厘米3的平方基体。什么基度使表面面积最小化?",
